				</figcaption>

				<p>
					A couple of features in Pointwise helped Siemon make the solutions more numerically stable: the Source feature enabled him to control the tetrahedra more tightly; while the ability to build quads provided greater resolution near the walls. 
				</p>

				<p>
					&ldquo;The nice thing about Pointwise is that it allows for more user input when building the grids and meshes,&rdquo; says Siemon. &ldquo;It gives me a much more active hand in building the block. I could refine the areas more tightly where I wanted more precise info.&rdquo;
				</p>

